<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="K" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Kindly2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Kindly,</orth> adv. (compar. <cit><quote>--er,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 24</bibl></cit>), 1) naturally, in a manner suited to the character or occasion: <cit><quote>shall not myself, one of their kind, be --er moved than thou art,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 24</bibl></cit>. <emph>this do, and do it k.</emph>  <bibl n="shak. shr 1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. I, 66</bibl>. <cit><quote>thou hast most k. hit it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 59</bibl></cit> (pertinently). Quibbling: <cit><quote>thy other daughter will use thee k.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.5.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 5, 15</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) in a benevolent and friendly manner, affectionately: <bibl n="shak. luc 253" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 253</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 4, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.207" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 207</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 4, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.141" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 15.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.78.15" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 4, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.5.104" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.40" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.346" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 346</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 24</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.2.33" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 1, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.4.62" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.9.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 9, 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.81" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.3.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 3, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 2, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.131" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 1, 131</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.5.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 5, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 6, 63</bibl>.
